Iran said on Thursday that it has sought financial assistance from the International Monetary Fund, which has not lent it money since 1962, to help it combat the novel coronavirus. “Our central bank requested access” to the IMF’s Rapid Financing Instrument (RFI), Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif said on Twitter, urging the fund’s board to respond to the request “responsibly”. AFP Iran president slams US for spreading 'fear' over virus Coronavirus: Iranian MP ‘dies of flu’ as death toll rises to 43 in Iran Iran coronavirus deaths jump to 26, Vice President infected, Friday prayers cancelled